To securely access the Storage account, we create a NIC Card. Inside the Storage account, we create NFS for Linux machine, SMB for Windows. With this WIndows VM can access the Storage account securely and Linux VM can access the Storage account.

Settings in Storage account/File share
No Root squash - If you are root, you are having root access(root access is retained) over the mounted NFS Drives. You can delete the satya files if though you are Ravi(root person) - NON CRITICAL DATA
Root squash - Root is also mapped as anonymous user. Cannot delete Satya's file. You are Ravi - MEDIUM CRITICAL DATA.
All Squash - All users are mapped as anonymous users. Highly recommended for Secure Infra. So, even though you are root, you will not have access over others resources, in case access is needed, you need to request - FULL CRITICAL DATA

